article.headline: Missouri St. 63, Bethune-Cookman 49
article.story: SPRINGFIELD, Mo. (AP) -- Four Missouri State players scored in double figures Wednesday night to lead the Bears to a 63-49 win over Bethune-Cookman in the second round of the Las Vegas Classic. Chris Cooks and Deven Mitchell had 12 points each, while Dale Lamberth had 11 and Spencer Laurie added 10. Missouri State (7-3) watched its 29-22 halftime lead disappear after Bethune-Cookman (4-6) scored the first eight points of the second half to go up 30-29 with 14:52 left. But Missouri State exploded with a 26-7 run to pull away to a 55-37 lead with 6:38 remaining. Missouri State outrebounded the Wildcats 41-23 and scored 22 points off Bethune-Cookman turnovers. Bethune-Cookman was led by Dewayne Pettus with 17 points and John Holmes added 13.
